13. Reguli : Regulus, being taken captive by the Carthagini· ans, was sent to Rome on parole of honour, to treat of an ex- change of prisoners. Instead of advising this measure, by which he would himself have been restored to his, country, he dissuaded the senate from it, as against their interest to ex- change the young and vigorous Carthaginians for the less effi- cient Romans. He returned and surrendered himself to his enemies 3 who, being enraged at his conduct, put him to death by the most cruel tortures.
